# Architecture (Rails 8 + SQLite + Hotwire)

Full-stack Rails app for the **Portal Publicidad Activa** MVP: inventario buscable sobre el crawl del portal nacional (Capa 1), con enlaces oficiales y curación Civio—not a replacement for transparencia.gob.es.

**Stack:** Rails 8 · SQLite · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS 4 · Turbo · Stimulus  
**Spec:** `../docs/publicidad-activa-mvp.md` (paths relative to monorepo root)

## App layout

- **app/controllers/** – HTTP only: params → domain services/models → render.
- **app/views/** – ERB templates; Spanish UI; human labels next to slugs (`rpt-mdef` → «Defensa · RPT»).
- **app/javascript/** – `application.ts`, Stimulus controllers in `controllers/*.ts`, built to `app/assets/builds/`.
- **app/assets/stylesheets/** – Tailwind entry (`application.tailwind.css`).
- **app/models/application_record.rb** – Base for all domain models. No other files in `app/models/`.
- **app/domains/** – Business domains (see `domain_structure.mdc`): `resources`, `organisms`, `curation`, `search`.
- **lib/** – Import helpers, rake task bodies that delegate to domain services.
- **data/** – Curated JSON (`organismos.json`, `fuentes-civio.json`); generated index optional until DB import exists.

## Target routes (MVP)

Align controllers with product routes (names may vary):

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `/` | Home: stats, six materias, entry to search |
| `/explore` | Global search + facets (default **vigente**; histórico behind toggle) |
| `/explore/:materia`, `/explore/:materia/:subtema` | Browse by taxonomy + counts |
| `/organisms`, `/organisms/:code` | List + ficha (resources + portal ministerio link) |
| `/url-map` | Technical tree (port or link to `docs/publicidad-activa-url-map.html`) |

Use Turbo Frames/Streams where they simplify filters and search without a separate SPA.

## Controllers

- Thin actions: strong params, one service call, render or redirect.
- No business logic, no N+1-heavy querying in controllers—push to services/queries with `includes`.
- Prefer server-rendered HTML for MVP; JSON only for explicit APIs (chat widget, etc.).

## Domain models and services

Same rules as API-style domains:

- Models in `app/domains/<name>/models/`, flat: validations, associations, scopes, cheap predicates.
- Workflows, import, search, and cross-entity rules in **services** (or queries).
- `# frozen_string_literal: true` in every Ruby file.
- `self.table_name` set explicitly on each model.
- Transactions in services when import or updates touch multiple tables.

## SQLite

- Schema changes via `db/migrate/`. Keep migrations reversible when possible.
- Index foreign keys and columns used in `WHERE`, `ORDER`, and facet counts.
- Use appropriate types (`text` for URLs, `integer` for enums, ISO date strings or integers for periodo ordering as needed).
- Solid Cache / Solid Queue / Solid Cable use separate schema files under `db/`—do not mix app domain tables into those files.

## Data pipeline

1. Source: `docs/publicidad-activa-url-map.html` (embedded `DATA` tree).
2. Flatten to resource records (url, materia, subtema, organismoCode, vigencia, periodo, depth, …).
3. Load via `Resources::Services::ImportFromCrawl` (or rake invoking it)—single canonical path into DB.
4. Enrich display with `curation` + `organisms` data at read time or during import.

Team contract: one search implementation (`Search::Services::SearchResources`) used by UI and any chat integration.

## Frontend (TypeScript + Stimulus + Tailwind)

- Stimulus controllers: one concern per controller (`search_controller.ts`, `filters_controller.ts`); register in `controllers/index.ts`.
- Prefer progressive enhancement: works without JS where possible; Stimulus for facets, toggles, debounced search.
- Tailwind utility classes in views; avoid custom CSS unless necessary.
- Run `bin/dev` for Rails + JS/CSS watchers; builds output to `app/assets/builds/`.

## Ruby quality

- Keyword arguments for multi-arg public APIs.
- Enums for fixed sets (`vigencia`, `hosting` when stored).
- Model validations for single-record invariants; service validation for import/search rules.
- Request/system tests for critical flows; unit tests for services and import edge cases.

## Out of scope for this app (do not expand into)

- Mirroring PDF/HTML from ministerios.
- Crawling all autonomic portals (Capa 2) in MVP.
- Portal de Contratación deep search (CPV, expedientes).
- OPP-2 / derecho de acceso flows.
- AI-generated journalistic or legal text.

## Summary

- **Controllers + views**: Spanish UX, thin wiring, official outbound links.
- **Domains**: `resources`, `organisms`, `curation`, `search`—all non-trivial logic here.
- **SQLite + migrations**: indexed schema for ~1.2k+ resources and facets.
- **Import**: crawl at repo root → services → DB; curated JSON in `data/`.
- **Frontend**: Turbo + Stimulus + Tailwind; TypeScript in `app/javascript/`.
